    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> It you just define them with a noop, everything is broken :p.\n\nYes that's on purpose, once you use the hook, you need to call the search function/call the callback. That's the API exposed so that you can implement complex patterns with it (debounce, min length, act on helper, do an asynchronous call to an API..).\n\n> My point is that we should be able to clearly know which kind of method we're dealing with from their name. Do you think that would be a good idea?\n\nYes, as you said:\n- we have **events**. As for libs I use, events are better being things that you can only listen to, only the DOM provides things like events + event object you can cancel. But only given the complexity of those.\n- we have hooks (searchFunction, queryHook), we could maybe call them that way, searchHook, queryHook\n- then we have formatData but I am not sure there's a need to change anything to it, we did not have issues about it or misunderstanding. The only one being that people would like to reformat the whole dataset, not per hit (thats another topic)\n\nWe could just rename searchFunction to searchHook but unsure this is the biggest pain, you tried to go to the searchBox to implement something that belongs to the whole instance, that's maybe the real issue?\n",
